activity.text:
It looks like it might have been introduced by the recent pull request: https://github.com/coronasafe/care_fe/pull/7305.

The `renderFileUpload` method [new includes](https://github.com/coronasafe/care_fe/blob/f39ce8344e7087cfe3288fcabc761cd671221df0/src/Components/Patient/FileUpload.tsx#L579-L580) the following:

```tsx
  <span className="font-semibold leading-relaxed">
    File Name:{" "}
  </span>{" "}
  {item.name}
  {item.extension}
```

but previously it was:

```tsx
 <div>
  <span className="font-semibold leading-relaxed">
    File Name:{" "}
  </span>{" "}
  {item.name}
</div>
```


but name as stored in `FileUpload.name` already has `.pdf` extension, added in:

https://github.com/coronasafe/care/blob/8616f5c956f0ee8f252ea5f0581bb1fd2dff986f/care/facility/utils/reports/discharge_summary.py#L180-L185

Would it be better to change it on back-end or frond-end? My thinking is that it may be better fixing it on front-end, as on back-end it was working okay, it communicates with S3 so I'm not sure what implication would be for changing file name pattern. Front-end uses files taken from S3 and the code adding second ".pdf" extension is a new addition so changing it should not cause much issues for the whole system.

I saw that there were no tests for this part of code. Would you accept a pull request adding a test? I may have time over the weekend to add it.
